Harrison Street, east from Washington, across Greenwich (Ninth Ave. Elevated Line thereon) to Hudson Streets.

January 9, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

Harrison Street, west from Washington to West Streets. Shown on the west side of the latter is the entrance to Pier No. 23 North (Hudson) River.

November 9, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

Harrison Street, east from Washington Street, showing this thoroughfare after the removal of street car tracks by the W.P.A. The photographer is viewing towards Hudson Street. The 9th Avenue "El " appears on Greenwich Street and is running north and south.

April 28, 1937

W.P.A.Photo
Five Boroughs Project

Washington Street, south from Harrison Street, showing Manhattans wholesale produce zone prior to a street car-track removal project. To the right center appears the upper portion of the N.Y.Telephone Building. (No. 140 West Street).

April 28, 1937

W.P.A.Photo
